This is the first bug fix release for our 3.12.x series.
There aren&rsquo;t any &ldquo;super critical must upgrade&rdquo; bugs fixed, so updating isn&rsquo;t urgent. &#x1f604;
Downloads DB.Browser.for.SQLite-3.12.1-win32-v2.msi - Standard (MSI) installer for Win32 and WinXP DB.Browser.for.SQLite-3.12.1-win32.zip - .zip (no installer) for Win32 and WinXP DB.Browser.for.SQLite-3.12.1-win64-v2.msi - Standard (MSI) installer for Win64 DB.Browser.for.SQLite-3.12.1-win64.zip - .zip (no installer) for Win64 DB.Browser.for.SQLite-3.12.1-v2.dmg - For macOS The changes in this over the 3.12.0 release include:

The macOS installer for 3.11.1 has been updated, so now when the application runs it does so in &ldquo;light theme mode&rdquo; (the Aqua look) on macOS Mojave. &#x1f604;
https://download.sqlitebrowser.org/DB.Browser.for.SQLite-3.11.1v2.dmg
It&rsquo;s a workaround for anyone using Mojave in Dark mode, which Qt doesn&rsquo;t yet properly support. Without this workaround, the colour pallete was unusable in important places. eg white on white when browsing data &#x1f626;
Jesse Jackson, thank you so much for showing us how to fix this problem.

It turned out our previous &ldquo;new&rdquo; project name was already taken. Oops.
So, our project has now been renamed to &ldquo;DB Browser for SQLite&rdquo;.
Hopefully this is the final rename. &#x1f604;
